efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N*M) where N is the number of operations and M is the length of the word after all operations.
space complexity: O(N*M)
energy implications: LOW 
explanation: The solution iterates through the operations, performing the corresponding action on the word. The word is built up character by character, and the final character at index k-1 is returned. The time complexity is dominated by the string concatenation and character manipulation within the loop. The space complexity is also dominated by the growth of the word string.

